A man in Bondo has died after he allegedly set himself ablaze. Edwin Omondi, 44, was found dead in his house this morning after neighbours saw smoke emanating from the roof of his house. When they broke in they found the man already dead. The incident occurred at Ochong’a estate in Bondo sub-county. Bondo OCPD Paul Kiarie said preliminary report suggests the man might have used petrol to set his body ablaze. Kiarie, however, revealed that few household items and his motorbike were salvaged from the house. He said the deceased who was earning a living as a photographer is suspected to have committed suicide. The body has been removed to Bondo sub-county hospital mortuary. Click here for the latest political news 